server.movement.TeleportMovement;\r\nimport tools.data.input.LittleEndianAccessor;\r\n\r\npublic abstract class AbstractMovementPacketHandler extends AbstractMaplePacketHandler {\r\n\r\n    protected List<LifeMovementFragment> parseMovement(LittleEndianAccessor lea) {\r\n        List<LifeMovementFragment> res = new ArrayList<>();\r\n        byte numCommands = lea.readByte();\r\n        for (byte i = 0; i < numCommands; i++) {\r\n            byte command = lea.readByte();\r\n            switch (command) {\r\n                case 0: // normal move\r\n                case 5:\r\n                case 12:\r\n                case 14:\r\n                case 35:\r\n                case 36:\r\n                {\r\n                    short xpos = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short ypos = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short xwobble = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short ywobble = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short unk = lea.readShort();\r\n                    if (command == 12) {\r\n                        byte newstate = lea.readByte();\r\n                        short duration = lea.readShort();\r\n                        AbsoluteLifeMovement alm = new AbsoluteLifeMovement(command, new Point(xpos, ypos), duration, newstate);\r\n                        alm.setUnk(unk);\r\n                        alm.setPixelsPerSecond(new Point(xwobble, ywobble));\r\n                        res.add(alm);\r\n                        break;\r\n                    }\r\n                }\r\n                case 1:\r\n                case 2:\r\n                case 13: // Shot-jump-back thing\r\n                case 16: // Float\r\n                case 17:\r\n\t\t\t\tcase 18:\r\n\t\t\t\tcase 19: // Springs on maps\r\n                case 20: // Aran Combat Step\r\n                case 21:\r\n                case 22:\r\n                case 23:\r\n                case 24:\r\n                case 25:\r\n                case 26:\r\n                case 27:\r\n                case 28:\r\n                case 29:\r\n                case 30:\r\n                case 31:\r\n                case 32:\r\n                case 33:\r\n                case 34:\r\n                {\r\n                    short xpos = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short ypos = lea.readShort();\r\n                    byte newstate = lea.readByte();\r\n                    short duration = lea.readShort();\r\n                    RelativeLifeMovement rlm = new RelativeLifeMovement(command, new Point(xpos, ypos), duration, newstate);\r\n                    res.add(rlm);\r\n                    break;\r\n                }\r\n                case 3:\r\n                case 4: // tele... -.-\r\n                case 6: // fj\r\n                case 7: // assaulter\r\n                case 8: // assassinate\r\n                case 9: // rush\r\n\t\t\t\tcase 11: //chair\r\n                {\r\n                    short xpos = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short ypos = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short xwobble = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short ywobble = lea.readShort();\r\n                    byte newstate = lea.readByte();\r\n                    TeleportMovement tm = new TeleportMovement(command, new Point(xpos, ypos), newstate);\r\n                    tm.setPixelsPerSecond(new Point(xwobble, ywobble));\r\n                    res.add(tm);\r\n                    break;\r\n                }\r\n                case 10: // Change Equip\r\n                    res.add(new ChangeEquip(lea.readByte()));\r\n                    break;\r\n                case 15: { \r\n                    short xpos = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short ypos = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short xwobble = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short ywobble = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short unk = lea.readShort();\r\n                    short fh = lea.readShort();\r\n                    byte newstate = lea.readByte();\r\n                    short duration = lea.readShort();\r\n                    JumpDownMovement jdm = new JumpDownMovement(command, new Point(xpos, ypos), duration, newstate);\r\n                    jdm.setUnk(unk);\r\n                    jdm.setPixelsPerSecond(new Point(xwobble, ywobble));\r\n                    jdm.setFH(fh);\r\n                    res.add(jdm);\r\n                    break;\r\n                }\r\n                default:\r\n\t\t\t\t\tSystem.out.println(\"Unhandled Case:\" + command);\r\n                    return null;\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        return res;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    protected void updatePosition(List<LifeMovementFragment> movement, AnimatedMapleMapObject target, int yoffset) {\r\n        for (LifeMovementFragment move : movement) {\r\n            if (move instanceof LifeMovement) {\r\n                if (move instanceof AbsoluteLifeMovement) {\r\n                    Point position = ((LifeMovement) move).getPosition();\r\n                    position.y += yoffset;\r\n                    target.setPosition(position);\r\n                }\r\n                target.setStance(((LifeMovement) move).getNewstate());\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n using over 2b HP with boss bars\r\n\r\n    public static byte[] showBossHP(int oid, long currHP, long maxHP, byte tagColor, byte tagBgColor) {\r\n        final MaplePacketLittleEndianWriter mplew = new MaplePacketLittleEndianWriter();\r\n        //int min = (int) ((currHP * 1000f / maxHP));\r\n        int min = (int) (1000 * ((double) currHP / (double) maxHP));\r\n        mplew.writeShort(SendOpcode.FIELD_EFFECT.getValue());\r\n        mplew.write(5);\r\n        mplew.writeInt(oid);\r\n        mplew.writeInt(min);\r\n        mplew.writeInt(1000);\r\n        mplew.write(tagColor);\r\n        mplew.write(tagBgColor);\r\n        return mplew.getPacket();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public static byte[] customShowBossHP(byte call, int oid, long currHP, long maxHP, Here is where the problem happens:\r\n\r\nThe game does not let UAs add skill points (if they are under a certain level) into their 2nd/3rd job skills because the Cygnus Knight skills are \"taking away\" the usable SPs and rendering the remaining unusable.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nSuppose I am a level 50 UA Assassin, with Vampire at level 20 (because it was given).\r\nI have 61 SP in my Skill tab (I've applied all 1st job SP), but I can only assign 41 of them. As you can imagine, the remaining 20 SP cannot be assigned into 2nd job anymore due to the client message \"You're lacking Level 1 Skills.\" From what we can tell, its because the game checks how many skill points have been assigned to 2nd job and will not let you use more than 61 at this level.\r\n\r\nI know this is likely a client-sided issue and may require client modding (or we add a low-key command line SP setter which isn't the best UX), but curious how many Rebirth servers get around this issue. \r\n\r\nAlso I'd like to extend my thanks on behalf of our small team for your work on break; //i believe it's any order\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        if (quest != null && found && item != null && item.getQuantity() > 0 && item.getItemId() == itemId)
